etymologies: Middle English; earliest use found in Arthour and Merlin. From down- + falling, after to fall down

definitions: The action of falling down; especially decline in power, status, or prosperity; downfall, demise.
The setting of the sun; the closing of the day; the onset of night. rare after 16th century.

etymologies: late 16th century; earliest use found in John Foxe (?1517–1587), martyrologist. From down- + falling, after to fall down and downfall

definitions: That is falling down or in a downward direction; (also figurative) that is falling into disgrace or ruin; declining, decaying.
